        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101201">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1101201" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101201.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Spicer Solo Clutch</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. CLUTCH COVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. ADJUSTING RINGS</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. REAR DRIVEN DISC</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. INTERMEDIATE PLATE</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. FRONT DRIVEN DISC</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. DRIVEN DISC DAMPER SPRINGS</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. POSITIVE SEPARATOR PINS</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. PRESSURE PLATE SPACERS</callout1>
                        <callout1>9. WEAR INDICATOR</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>The Spicer 15-1/2 inch Solo clutch is an adjustment-free, pull type clutch specifically engineered
                    for heavy duty truck applications with flat-flywheel diesel engines.
                </para>
                <para>The Solo clutch is available with dampened ceramic driven discs in 1-3/4 or 2 inch spline size.
                    Driven disc damper options are 6, 7, 9 and 10 spring designs.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
